items.summary:
**MACRO/MARKETS:** AI-driven equity rally and consumer strength reigniting M&A/IPO pipelines, reversing 2023 drought. Fee recovery signals confidence in growth narratives, though valuation multiples and policy uncertainty (rates, regulation) remain tail risks for deal velocity sustainability.

**CREDIT RISK:** Rising M&A activity increases leveraged finance exposure; ECL models must stress-test covenant deterioration post-close and refinancing risk in rate-sensitive deals. PD/LGD recalibration needed if leverage cycles compress post-integration.

**AI/ML:** Banks deploying ML for deal sourcing, target valuation models, and synergy prediction;
